      "sha256": "ee9df005f450e63d6693b4a61001f2c4b79c05e2e6c9d561bcb763e7d4e8c5fc",
      "source_region": "div.problem-additional-text",
      "text": "A conjecture of Erd\\H{o}s and Sauer."
    },
    "statement": {
      "sha256": "160e3174eb2ee250714ccc8dbc76148963c727f49444a0af9de693c5d12efc4c",
      "source_region": "div#content",
      "text": "Let $\\mathrm{ex}_r(n;K_{r+1}^r)$ be the maximum number of $r$-edges that can be placed on $n$ vertices without forming a $K_{r+1}^r$ (the $r$-uniform complete graph on $r+1$ vertices).\n\nIs every $r$-hypergraph $G$ on $n$ vertices the union of at most $\\mathrm{ex}_{r}(n;K_{r+1}^r)$ many copies of $K_r^r$ and $K_{r+1}^r$, no two of which share a $K_r^r$?"
    }
  },
